Bandits have attacked a community in Kaduna, killing two persons and taking 16 others away. The assailants on motorcycles raided Sabon Gero in the Millennium City area of the metropolis late Tuesday. Commander of the civilian Joint Task Force (JTF) and a resident of the area were killed in the attack, while a medical doctor was among those abducted. The bandits, it was learnt, stormed the community around past 10pm and started shooting indiscriminately.   Inmate graduates with 2nd Class Upper from Open University     After N2.5m fine, court threatens Evans with more penalties     Police kill two gunmen in Anambra   The Nation learnt that the JTF commander and other members immediately opened fire on the bandits but fell into the hoodlums’ ambush and the commander was shot dead. A resident of the community said, “The bandits opened fire and hit the commander in the legs and he fell down, then they shot him in the head. A resident was also hit and he died on the way to hospital.” He said the bandits might have targeted the house of a medical doctor in the area as they went straight to his residence and abducted him and six members of his family. “They stormed other houses and abducted nine other people, he added. A member of the JTF who gave his name as Isa Usman confirmed that their commander had been killed by the bandits. “We took his body to his wife and later buried him,” he said.